    <ListOfValue ID="AC_ACESImportHandlingUPDATE" ParentID="AC_LOV" AllowUserValueAddition="false" UseValueID="true">
      <Name QualifierID="en-US">ACES Import Handling UPDATE</Name>
      <Validation BaseType="text" MinValue="" MaxValue="" MaxLength="2000" InputMask=""/>
      <ValueGroup ID="PARTIAL">
        <Value>Partial Replacement: 
      Evaluate the combinations of Brand, Part Terminology, and Base Vehicle of each record provided in the file. 
      For each combination found, replace all records in the database with those in the input file.</Value>
      </ValueGroup>
      <ValueGroup ID="STANDARD">
        <Value>Standard Update: 
      Delete records with action="D" 
      Add records with action="A"</Value>
      </ValueGroup>
    </ListOfValue>
    <ListOfValue ID="AC_ACESImportHandlingFULL" ParentID="AC_LOV" AllowUserValueAddition="false" UseValueID="true">
      <Name QualifierID="en-US">ACES Import Handling FULL</Name>
      <Validation BaseType="text" MinValue="" MaxValue="" MaxLength="2000" InputMask=""/>
      <ValueGroup ID="BRAND_PART_TERMINOLOGY">
        <Value>Brand + Part Terminology: 
      Replacement of application records is within the brand and part terminology. 
      All applications for a particular brand are replaced for all part terminologies that are present in the input file. 
      Applications for part terminologies NOT in the input file are left untouched.</Value>
      </ValueGroup>
      <ValueGroup ID="BRAND_PART_NUMBER">
        <Value>Brand + Part Number: 
      Replacement of application records is within the brand and part number. 
      All applications for a particular brand are replaced for all part numbers that are in the input file. 
      Applications for part numbers that are NOT in the input file are left untouched.</Value>
      </ValueGroup>
      <ValueGroup ID="BRAND">
        <Value>Brand: 
      Replacement of application records is within the brand. 
      All applications for all brands in the input file are replaced, regardless of part terminology.</Value>
      </ValueGroup>
    </ListOfValue>
